listings.Name: Test Multi AMI and Comm
listings.Building_Selection_Criteria:
Ability to pay rent standard – income must be 2 times the monthly rent for affordable units.  PBV units referred by SFHA, there is no minimum income requirements.

Criminal History Standard – We will consider qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records in accordance with San Francisco Police Code Article 49 – Fair Chance Ordinance.  Applications will be processed per the Fair Chance Ordinance procedures outlined in the Resident Selection Criteria.  

Minimum Household Size Rule - Households must be at least as many people as there are bedrooms in the unit to apply. 

Maximum Household Size Standard – 1 bedroom 3 persons, 2 bedrooms 5 persons and 3 bedrooms 7 persons

Other – Complete Resident Selection Criteria can be viewed by visiting www.mercyhousing.org/CA-Transbay7
